description:
This is a new version of GUI notepad. It has a lot of updates compared to previous public release 1.2.

Note to Windows 10/11 users: You must disable Windows Terminal and enable legacy console for this batch file to work correctly.

To disable Windows Terminal and enable Windows Console Host:
1. Win + R, type "wt" and press Enter to launch Windows Terminal (if nothing happens/you get an error, search for Windows Terminal on the start menu, if still nothing comes up then you're already done)
2. Click the arrow next to the plus symbol and then click "Settings"
3. Change the "Default terminal application" to Windows Console Host
4. Click "Save"

To enable legacy mode, do the following:
1. Run the GUI_notepad.bat batch file
2. Right click on the window title bar
3. Click on "Properties"
4. Make sure  "Use legacy console" is checked then click "OK"
5. Close the batch file and command window
6. Re-open GUI_notepad.bat batch file

Changelog:
+ Added a splash screen (can be turned off with a shortcut)
+ Added command line interface ('GUI_notepad /?' for syntax)
+ Added fun facts on the start screen
+ Added light color switch in the color dialog
+ Added find option in the edit menu
+ Added replace option in the edit menu
+ Added .suffix. and .prefix. tags when editing text (use both of them at the beginning of a line to add a suffix or a prefix)
+ Added status prompts (for loading, saving, clearing, etc.)
+ Added built in BG.EXE (only works in command line with Windows Vista or later)
+ Added error message for a missing BG.EXE
- Removed about dialog, replaced with a full screen message
* Improved about screen
* Improved view menu
* Updated tutorial
* Now supports basically unlimited notes
* Bug fixes
? Backwards compatibility with older GUI notepad formats
? Batch file store version (same, but with a different message on splash screen)
